  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Risk factors for difficult intubation are well described in anesthesiology. But intubation in
      the intensive care unit (ICU) is a challenging issue, associated with severe life-threatening
      complications. Non-anesthesiologist trainees performing ICU intubation may not fully
      appreciate the potential difficulty and complications.

      Therefore in this retrospective analysis the MACOCHA score will be used to determine
      difficult intubation in the ICU and predict intubation failure.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
